## 6. EXECUTION FLOW

### Application Boot
```
Browser loads index.html
  → Vite serves /src/main.jsx
  → ReactDOM.createRoot mounts <App /> under <React.StrictMode>
  → BrowserRouter reads current URL
  → Routes match URL to Login / Signup / Workspace
```

### Login Flow (Current — Mocked)
```
User visits /login
  → Login.jsx renders two-panel layout
  → User fills email + password (uncontrolled)
  → Submits form
  → handleLogin() called → navigate('/') → BLANK PAGE (bug)
```

### Signup Flow
```
User visits /signup
  → Signup.jsx renders registration form
  → User fills all fields (uncontrolled, no validation)
  → Submits form
  → handleSignup() → navigate('/login') ← correct
```

### Main Workspace Flow
```
User visits /workspace
  → Workspace.jsx renders
  → Sidebar + TopBar always visible
  → activeView === 'dashboard' → DashboardArea shown by default
      → User clicks "Start New Lesson"
          → handleNewLesson() → setActiveView('chat')
          → ChatArea replaces DashboardArea
              → Pre-seeded messages rendered via MessageBubble
              → SuggestedPrompts shown (messages ≤ 3)
              → User types in ChatInput → Enter / Send button
                  → handleSendMessage(text) called
                  → User message appended to messages[]
                  → isTyping = true → typing indicator shown
                  → setTimeout 1500ms
                  → Simulated AI response appended
                  → isTyping = false
                  → messagesEndRef scrolls into view
```

